title: Lulu Exchange opens branch in Seychelles
text: Lulu Exchange opens branch in Seychelles By ET Bureau | 8 Oct, 2015, 03.58PM IST   KOCHI: Lulu Exchange Limited, a leading global remittance and foreign exchange brand, commenced operations of its first branch in Seychelles in Victoria. The branch was inaugurated by Sanjay Panda, high commissioner of India to the Republic of Seychelles in the presence of Adeeb Ahamed, director, Lulu Exchange Limited . Speaking on the occasion, Adeeb Ahamed, who is also the managing director of LuLu Forex Pvt. Ltd. India, said, "This is the ninth country of our presence. We had started out with a single branch in 2009, and today with this opening we have 110 outlets globally." Lulu Exchange Limited has partnered with internationally renowned and trusted money transfer service providers and the new branch will help the company to strengthen its global position, he added." We are committed to fair business practices and are fully compliant with global anti-money laundering protocols."
